Here's your statistical EDA checklist for the Uber project:

 Shapiro-Wilk — test if demand distribution is normal
 Mann-Whitney U test — weekend vs weekday demand, is the difference real?
 Spearman correlation — which features actually correlate with demand?
 ACF/PACF plots — which lags are statistically significant (replaces guessing)
 ADF test — is your demand series stationary or does it have a trend?
 Zone comparison — t-test or Mann-Whitney between high vs low demand zones

All doable in Python with scipy.stats and statsmodels. Come back when you've run these and I'll help you interpret the results.

